Marli van Breda was struck several times on the head and her throat was slashed in January in her family's South African home . 
  Her father Martin and mother Teresa were killed and her brother Rudi escaped with minor injuries . 
  Marli suffered severe brain damage and has no memory of the attack . 
  She was released from hospital last month and is now in rehabilitation . 
  Her family said she is able to walk and talk but has retrograde amnesia . 
  The attack took place in the family home in Stellenbosch on January 27 . 
 